<br />
The important part of the Infected is that they eventually die.  They go through their stages, and at some point they become spore clouds.  None of the groups of humans were shown to really have a problem with the Infected, they had problems when they went outside to scavenge.  If you remove the need to scavenge, and migrate to cleanup, you solve the problem.  Decades later if/when someone got infected, they would be put down fairly quickly by everyone around them holding weapons and handcuffs.  Oh, you might be infected?  Well lets just handcuff your wrist and ankle together and wait it out.</blockquote>
